<h1 class="mb-4">Larify Documentation</h1>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Getting Started</div>
  <p>Welcome to Larify, a Laravel-like framework for Node.js. This guide will help you understand how to use the framework effectively.</p>
  
  <h3>Installation</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Clone the repository: <code>git clone https://github.com/yourusername/larify.git</code></li>
    <li>Install dependencies: <code>npm install</code></li>
    <li>Copy .env.example to .env: <code>cp .env.example .env</code></li>
    <li>Configure your database in the .env file</li>
    <li>Run migrations: <code>npm run migrate</code></li>
    <li>Start the server: <code>npm run dev</code></li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Framework Structure</div>
  <p>Larify follows Laravel's directory structure to make it familiar for PHP developers:</p>
  
  <h4>Core Directories</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>app/</strong> - Application logic</li>
    <li><strong>config/</strong> - Configuration files</li>
    <li><strong>database/</strong> - Database migrations</li>
    <li><strong>public/</strong> - Static assets</li>
    <li><strong>resources/</strong> - Views and assets</li>
    <li><strong>routes/</strong> - Route definitions</li>
    <li><strong>storage/</strong> - Logs and cache</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Command Line Interface</div>
  <p>Larify comes with a powerful CLI similar to Laravel's Artisan:</p>
  
  <h4>Available Commands</h4>
  <pre><code>node bin/larify make:controller UserController --resource
node bin/larify make:model User --migration
node bin/larify migrate
node bin/larify migrate:reset
node bin/larify serve</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">Next Steps</div>
  <p>Now that you have Larify up and running, here are some next steps:</p>
  
  <h4>Create Your First Controller</h4>
  <pre><code>node bin/larify make:controller BlogController --resource</code></pre>
  
  <h4>Define Routes</h4>
  <p>Add routes in <code>routes/web.js</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>router.get('/blog', BlogController.index);
router.get('/blog/:id', BlogController.show);</code></pre>
  
  <h4>Create Models and Migrations</h4>
  <pre><code>node bin/larify make:model Post --migration</code></pre>
</div>

